By Martins Ifijeh The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has confirmed three more cases of COVID-19 in Lagos State, bringing the number of recorded cases in the state Sunday to six, and the total number in the country to 30. Stating this on its Twitter handle Sunday, @NCDCgov, the centre said two of the cases were returning travellers while one was a contact of a confirmed case. It said: “As at 05:28 pm on March 22, there are 30 confirmed cases of #COVID19 in Nigeria. 2 have been discharged with no deaths.” More details later..